[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(13) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "And he also rebelled.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Kings 24:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Who had made him swear by God.—When Nebuchadnezzar appointed Zedekiah vassal-king of Judah, he would naturally make him swear fealty to himself by the God of his fathers. The fact is not specially recorded in Kings; but the prophet Ezekiel makes it the point of a prophecy against the king and his grandees (Ezekiel 17:11-21; comp, especially 2Chronicles 36:17, “mine oath that he hath despised.”)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Who had made him swear by God.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—When Nebuchadnezzar appointed Zedekiah vassal-king of Judah, he would naturally make him swear fealty to himself by the God of his fathers. The fact is not specially recorded in Kings; but the prophet Ezekiel makes it the point of a prophecy against the king and his grandees (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezekiel 17:11-21",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; comp, especially ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 36:17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", “mine oath that he hath despised.”)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But (and) stiffened his neck and hardened his heart.—(Comp. the like expression in Deuteronomy 2:30; 2Kings 17:14; Jeremiah 19:15.) Zedekiah was not personally unfavourable to the prophet Jeremiah, and consulted him more than once; but he was too weak and timorous to stand by the prophetic counsel, in defiance of his princes who were intriguing with Egypt.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "But",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "and",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "stiffened his neck and hardened his heart.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—(Comp. the like expression in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 2:30",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Kings 17:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 19:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) Zedekiah was not personally unfavourable to the prophet Jeremiah, and consulted him more than once; but he was too weak and timorous to stand by the prophetic counsel, in defiance of his princes who were intriguing with Egypt.",
            "children": []
